 voice with a simple touch on GPS screen. Real time playing recorded videos from memory card through GPS device. Considerate storage mode preserves recorded file not be lost immediately when power off.</span></div>\n</td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;"><img title="Integrated Driving Recorder (Optional)" src="http://www.garmin.co.in/m/_sized/m/in/g/products/nuvi2568lm_sh03_gdr-200x122.jpg" alt="Integrated Driving Recorder (Optional)" width="200" height="122" /></span></td>\n</tr><tr><td valign="top">\n<div style="border-bottom:#666 1px solid;padding:5px;font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">PC Tool Software (Optional)</span></div>\n<div style="padding:5px;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">Garmin self-developed PC tool software provides significant information below: images, maps, tracks, coordinates, time and speed. Data above provide the best reference back to accident scene. Garmin offers “point to point” comparison innovatively. Click track info to view correspondent image with relative position on map. Garmin provides a more efficient tool to compare data information.</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr></tbody></table><p><span style="font-size:10pt;"><strong> </strong></span></p>', '2016-05-27 16:05:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
(160, 137, 'Garmin GPS Navigator - Nuvi ® 2460LM (India)', 14490, 50, 'garmin-gps-navigator-nuvi-2460lm-india.jpg', '<h3> </h3>\n<h3><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">Advanced Series Navigation for Your Car</span></strong></h3>\n<ul><li><span style="font-size:10pt;">10.9cm display</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">Brand new user interface</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">Detailed maps of India with free lifetime¹ updates</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">Garmin photoReal Junction View</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">Preloaded with Travel Guide</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">Bluetooth compatible</span></li>\n</ul><p> </p>\n<h3><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">Bright Display</span></strong></h3>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">nüvi 2460LM has a bright 10.9cm display.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h3><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">Brand New User Interface</span></strong></h3>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">An advanced navigation engineproviding a faster, more intuitive user interfaceto enhance the speed, convenience andaccuracy of searches and routing for everydaydriving.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;"> </span></p>\n<h3><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">Detailed Maps with Free Updates</span></strong></h3>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">nüvi 2460LM arrives loaded with detailed maps of India. With free lifetime¹ map updates, your routes are sure to reflect the most up-to-date maps, POIs (points of interest) and navigation information.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;"> New maps are available for download up to 4 times per year, for the life of your device, with no fees.</span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">With so much data, nüvi 2460LM makes it easy to find addresses and 7.3 millions of POIs such as shops, restaurants and other destinations. nüvi 2460LM arrives preloaded with POIs, so there’s no need for you to enter that address information. </span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">Just select one — or many — and navigate there, quickly and easily. You also have the ability to add custom POIs to your nüvi 2460LM.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h3><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">Garmin photoReal Junction View</span></strong></h3>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">No more guessing which lane you need to be in to make an upcoming turn. photoReal junction view realistically displays junctions and interchanges along your route, including the surrounding landscape. </span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">Brightly colored arrows indicate the proper lane to drive. nüvi 2460LM also depicts real road signs as they appear along your route.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h3><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">More Information at a Glance</span></strong></h3>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">nüvi 2460LM keeps your driving map onscreen at all times and additional information appears alongside. For details, simply ask or touch the screen. </span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">As you drive your route, Up ahead constantly informs you of nearby services, including restaurants, fuel stations, hospitals and stores. </span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">nüvi 2460LM displays speed limit, current speed and accurate time of arrival. With a quick glance, you can read the name of your current street. </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;"> </span></p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">Plus, you’ll be surprised to see Point Of Interest icons on the maps and no need to page through menus.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;"> Have you ever had trouble finding the parking around you? Garmin brand new user interface will automatically provide parking information near your destination.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h3><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">Travel Guide</span></strong></h3>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">Plan your trip and travel with your Garmin navigator without the burden of travel books! Garmin Travel Guide now available in India, bringing you in-depth coverage of long standing historical monuments, and fine dining places.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<h3><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">Bluetooth® Compatible</span></strong></h3>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">Sync a Bluetooth-enabled device, such as your smartphone, to nüvi 2460LM for hands-free calling through its integrated microphone and speaker. </span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;">Safely stow your phone in a glove compartment, pocket or purse and still make and take calls without moving your hands from the steering wheel or your eyes from the road.</span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="5"><tbody><tr><td colspan="2" bgcolor="#ccddfc">\n<h3><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">Specifications</span></strong></h3>\n</td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Display size</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">10.9cm diag</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Display resolution</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">480x272 pixels</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Battery </span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">rechargeable lithium-ion </span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Battery life</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Up to 2.5 hrs</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">High-sensitiviy receiver</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Plreloaded street maps</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes, dual maps</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Free Liftime map updates</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">nuMaps Guarantees</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Ability to add maps</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Bult-in memory</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">4GB NAND flash</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Accepts data cards</span></td>\n<td width="166"><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes microSD™ card</span><br /><span style="font-size:10pt;"> (not included) </span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Waypoints/favorites/locations</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">1000</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Routes</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">100</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Voice prompts</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">10 languages</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Speaks street names</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes (Indian English)</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Lane Assist</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">myTrends</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Auto re-route</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Custom avoidance</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td width="212"><span style="font-size:10pt;">Route avoidance</span><br /><span style="font-size:10pt;"> (avoid highways, tolls etc.) </span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Bluetooth wireless technology</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Speed limit indicator</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">no</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Where am I?</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Trip planner</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">ecoRoute</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Custom POIs</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr bgcolor="#edf3fe"><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Garmin Garage</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr><tr><td><span style="font-size:10pt;">Photo Navigation</span></td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;">yes</span></td>\n</tr></tbody></table><p></p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;"> In the Box</span></strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<ul><li><span style="font-size:10pt;">nüvi 2460LM</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">Preloaded City Navigator® NT India and MalSing Maps</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">Lifetime maps¹</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">Vehicle power cable</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">Vehicle suction cup mount</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">USB cable</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;">Quick start manual</span></li>\n<li><span style="font-size:10pt;"> </span></li>\n</ul><p><span style="font-size:10pt;"><em>¹If you purchase a nüMaps Lifetime subscription (sold separately or bundled together with certain GPS models), you will receive up to 4 map data updates per year, when and as such updates are made available on Garmin’s website, for 1 compatible Garmin product until your product’s useful life expires or Garmin no longer receives map data from its third party supplier, whichever is shorter. </em></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;"><em>A product’s “useful life” means the period during which the product (a) has sufficient memory capacity and other required technical capabilities to utilize current map data and (b) is capable of operating as intended without major repairs. </em></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;"><em>A product will be deemed to be out of service and its useful life to be ended if no updates have been downloaded for such product for a period of 24 months or more. Unless otherwise stated, the updates you receive under the subscription will be updates to the same geographic map data originally included with your Garmin product when originally purchased.</em></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;"><em> In some instances, your Garmin product might not have sufficient memory remaining for you to load an update to the map data, in which case you will need to either (a) select reduced map data coverage for your updates, or (b) purchase separately a microSD™/SD™ card (if and as applicable to your Garmin product) and load all or a portion of the map data coverage for your updates to the card and insert the card into the microSD/SD card slot contained in your Garmin product.</em></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><span style="font-size:10pt;"><em>If neither of the measures in (a) or (b) can be used to address your product’s lack of sufficient remaining memory, then Garmin may conclude that the “useful life” of your product has expired. Garmin may terminate your nüMaps Lifetime subscription at any time if you violate any of the terms of this agreement or your subscription. Your nüMaps Lifetime subscription may not be transferred to another Garmin product.</em></span></p>\n<p> </p>\n<p><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;"><em>Functions</em></span></strong></p>\n<p> </p>\n<table cellpadding="5"><tbody><tr><td valign="top">\n<div style="border-bottom:#666 1px solid;padding:5px;font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;"><strong><span style="font-size:10pt;">Junction View</span></strong></div>\n<div style="padding:5px;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">No more guessing which lane you need to be in to make an upcoming turn. photoReal view junction view guides you to the correct lane for an approaching turn or exit, making unfamiliar intersections and exits easy to navigate. It realistically displays junctions on your route along with arrows that indicate the proper lane for navigation.</span></div>\n</td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;"><img title="Junction View" src="http://www.garmin.co.in/m/_sized/m/in/g/products/nuvi2568lm_sh01_jcv_1-200x114.png" alt="Junction View" width="200" height="113" /></span></td>\n</tr><tr><td valign="top">\n<div style="border-bottom:#666 1px solid;padding:5px;font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">Lane Info</span></div>\n<div style="padding:5px;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">Lane info on the upper left leads you the exact direction. No more guessing which lane you need to be in to make an upcoming turn.</span></div>\n</td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;"><img title="Lane Info" src="http://www.garmin.co.in/m/_sized/m/in/g/products/nuvi2568lm_sh02_laneinfo_1-200x114.png" alt="Lane Info" width="200" height="113" /></span></td>\n</tr><tr><td valign="top">\n<div style="border-bottom:#666 1px solid;padding:5px;font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">Hands-free Calling</span></div>\n<div style="padding:5px;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">It integrates Bluetooth® wireless technology with a built-in microphone and speaker. Talk hands-free through the 2465 while staying focused on the road.</span></div>\n</td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;"><img title="Hands-free Calling" src="http://www.garmin.co.in/m/_sized/m/in/g/products/in_nuvi2465_screen_001-200x114.jpg" alt="Hands-free Calling" width="200" height="113" /></span></td>\n</tr><tr><td valign="top">\n<div style="border-bottom:#666 1px solid;padding:5px;font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">myTrends</span></div>\n<div style="padding:5px;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">myTrends™ learns your driving habits and automatically predicts arrival times for your favorite places.</span></div>\n</td>\n<td><span style="font-size:10pt;"><img title="myTrends" src="http://www.garmin.co.in/m/_sized/m/in/g/products/in_nuvi2565_screen_005-200x114.jpg" alt="myTrends" width="200" height="113" /></span></td>\n</tr><tr><td valign="top">\n<div style="border-bottom:#666 1px solid;padding:5px;font-size:18px;font-weight:bold;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">Custom avoidance</span></div>\n<div style="padding:5px;"><span style="font-size:10pt;">To add avoid area or road and nüvi2460LM will prevent selection.</span></div>\n</td>\n</tr></tbody></table><p><span style="font-size:10pt;"><em><br /></em></span></p>\n<p></p>\n<p></p>', '2016-05-27 16:05:44', '0000-00-00 00:00:00'),
